NAME
     i.group -  An imagery function that creates and edits groups
                and subgroups of imagery
                (GRASS Imagery Tool)

SYNOPSIS
     i.group

DESCRIPTION
     i.group allows the user to collect cell in an imagery group
     by assigning them to named subgroups or other groups.  This
     enables the user to run analyses on any combination of the
     cell in a group.  The user creates the groups and subgroups
     and selects the cell that are to reside in them.  Analyses
     such as i.points and i.rectify ask the user for the imagery
     group to be analyzed.  Analyses such as i.cluster and
     i.maxlik ask the user for the imagery group and imagery
     subgroup to be analyzed.

     The first menu in the i.group program asks the user to
     select a group.  If the group does not exist, the user will
     be asked if he or she would like to create a new group.

     This program edits imagery groups. You may add to, or remove
     from an imagery group.  You may also create new groups.
            Please enter the group to be created/modified

       GROUP: _____________ (enter 'list' for a list of groups)


         AFTER COMPLETING ALL ANSWERS, HIT <ESC> TO CONTINUE
                        (OR <Ctrl-C> TO EXIT)


     If the word list is entered, groups that have already been
     created in the current LOCATION and MAPSET(S) will be
     displayed.

     The second menu in i.group provides the user with the
     following options:

             1.    Select a different group
             2.    Edit group title
             3.    Include new cell files in the group
                   or remove cell files from the group
             4.    Assign colors to the group
             5.    Create a new subgroup within the group

                   RETURN to exit






